--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: ddabeb8ea613c6a4e9bfb0c5a3d2dbb9, type: 3}
  m_Name: OpenCase
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueSequence
  lines:
  - speakerName: Boss
    portrait: {fileID: 1984190853, guid: 1be9303cf68adf8469a107b28073a96a, type: 3}
    text: Did you see that? The fans spun for a second, then nothing. No display
      either.
    showOnRightSide: 0
  - speakerName: Boss
    portrait: {fileID: 1984190853, guid: 1be9303cf68adf8469a107b28073a96a, type: 3}
    text: That tells us a lot. A PC that won't POST usually means a problem with
      the RAM, CPU, or motherboard.
    showOnRightSide: 0
  - speakerName: Boss
    portrait: {fileID: -2004239264, guid: f8402f94a4b63d44d90bf003f6ad06e0, type: 3}
    text: And no display? That could be a dead GPU or the RAM is so bad the system
      can't even reach the graphics card.
    showOnRightSide: 0
  - speakerName: Boss
    portrait: {fileID: -2004239264, guid: f8402f94a4b63d44d90bf003f6ad06e0, type: 3}
    text: "We can't tell just by looking. We need to test one part at a time. Open
      the case \u2014 grab your screwdriver with [1] and start unscrewing the side
      panel."
    showOnRightSide: 0
